title: Do not fill in text fields with '0' values
message:
Do not fill in text fields with '0' values

If the field has not been filled out yet, putting a '0'
thus requires the user to delete it before typing in the value.
To make it simpler, do not populate the text fields if the
value is '0'.

title: Change how licenses are accepted on travis-ci
message:
Change how licenses are accepted on travis-ci

After updating the SDK version and support libraries used,
Travis-CI failed to build because the support license
was not being accepted. Others have found the same issue.
A workaround is to use the android tool directly and
accept the license and setup for use. This commit
does just that.

run the release config to reduce time.

title: Use reflection in Property copy constructor
message:
Use reflection in Property copy constructor

There was originally a typo:

To avoid this mistake and any potential future mistakes,
use reflection to make the copy. This will ensure that each
field is exactly copied over.
